{"questionId":"18602","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chlorine undergoes many reactions.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chlorine gas reacts with water to produce hypochlorous acid and hydrochloric acid.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>⇌</mo><mi>HClO</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">State the formula of the conjugate base of hypochlorous acid.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><msup><mi>ClO</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"18602","referenceCode":"20N.2.hl.TZ0.1c(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the formula of the conjugate base of hypochlorous acid.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases","8.1 Theories of acids and bases","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}